two axix are there in flex

we can change the direction of flex box using
flex-direction: row; is default
flex-direction: row-reverse (reverse the flex)

flex-direction: column/column-riverse
--------------------------

justify-content (along main axis)

flex-start (start of flex based on flex direction)
flex-end
flex-center
space-between
space-around

----------------------------

flex-wrap

wrap (avoid streaching, adjust content to next row/col)
wrap-reverse (reverse the flex direction and wrap)
noswrap (default, forcefully ajdust content)

---------------------------------

align-items (along across cross axix)

start (top of the flex)

---------------------------------

align content (controls space between row/columns)
(doesnt make changes if there is no WRAP)

center (if
justify-content-: center
align-items: center
align-items: flex-start
align-content: center (makes everythin to center in a row)
)

-----------------------------------

FLEX BASIS, GROW, SHRINK + (SHORTHAND)

flex-BASIS
-is HEIGHT of item when flex-direction is COLUMN
-is WIDTH of item when flex-direction is ROW

flex-GROW
-grow to fill the extra space
fill by HEIGHT if flex-direction is COLUMN
fill by WIDTH if flex-direction is ROW

flex-SHRINK
shrink element is there is no space

SHORTHAND
flex: GROW, SHRINK, BASIS
BASIS can be anyone which has units.
grow and shrink are unitless